Coin Flip

USE CASE Description

1. A Player at random offers a prediction of a coin flip. 
The other players gets the other option. The coin is flipped.
The correct guess win

Triggers

1. A player at random offers prediction of a coin flip

Actors

1. A player who makes the prediction
2. A player that gets the other option
3. Coin
4. Coin Game

Preconditions

1. 2 player are available
2. A coint is available

Goals

1. One player win and the other lose

Not Available

1. Failed Conclustion, Extensions (Alternatives)

Step of Execution

1. A player at random is picked to predict the coin flip
2. The player pick offers a prediction of the coin flip
3. The other player gets the other coin flip option
4. The coin is flipped and the result is provided
5. A winner and loser is picked
6. Offer to try again


